-------
 _
**SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:**
 _
On reacquisition, SCP-8487 should be forced onto its modified Foundation computer terminal (designated SCP-8487-House), inside Cell 14b at Site 92. SCP-8487 should be contained as SCP-8487-Core, with that being the only data stored on the entire SCP-8487-House system. Under no circumstances is SCP-8487 or its terminal to be connected to any other hardware, and Cell 14b is to be tested on a monthly basis for electromagnetic shielding integrity. No "SCRIPT" of any form (including clothing tags, "SCRIPT" tattoos, or Foundation keycards) is to enter Cell 14b. Cell 14b is to remain signless.
 _
Should an SG event be observed[[footnote]] Presumably by the AI-monitored camera pointed at the cell window [[/footnote]], an SCP-8487 attendant is to use the hardwired Delete function of SCP-8487-House until such action loses all effect. SCP-8487-House must receive no damage; as a failsafe, backup terminals are stored outside the containment cell for emergency data transfer. The destruction of SCP-8487-Core is considered a significant security failure.
 _
SCP-8487 is currently uncontained. To rectify this, an ongoing search for Joan Allison is being conducted by MTF Phi-9, "Consider It Done". MTF Phi-9 will remain active until Joan Allison has been detained or SCP-8487 located. 
 _
**DESCRIPTION:**
 _
SCP-8487 is a singular, distinct, continuous entity documented to have existed since at least 430 BCE (±60 years). The anomaly is entirely composed of physically realized information, such as human writing, and commonly presents as a group of symbols; when in physical contact with other created symbols, SCP-8487 is able to self-incorporate them. All information incorporable by SCP-8487 has been designated "SCRIPT"[[footnote]] (SCP-8487 Consumable Realized Information PolyTextual) [[/footnote]]. Incorporation involves SCP-8487 restructuring itself to maximize internal complexity and info-mobility with its newly available characters, words, and other elements. This constitutes a significant threat. Though on paper[[footnote]] Or similar traditional scripture [[/footnote]] the anomaly could be considered a slow nuisance, its compatibility with software has been theorized as a scaling risk to world-wide infrastructure.
 _
It is currently unknown if SCP-8487 is sapient, sentient, or even alive.
 _
**SCP-8487-Core:** Physically damaging the media containing SCP-8487 is possible, however, damage causing all content to become illegible does not neutralize the anomaly. Instead, it will consistently remanifest in the nearest pre-existing character. This behavior suggests SCP-8487 is functionally "immortal". Thus, the simplest legible form of the anomaly (a single grapheme, such as the letter "X") has been designated SCP-8487-Core.
SCP-8487-Core is prone to Spontaneous Growth (SG) events. These are variably frequent, occurring within months or minutes of one another, and happening instantaneously. During these events, at least 200 other graphemes from the same language[[footnote]] Or more generally, "designed information system" [[/footnote]] will appear around SCP-8487 in its medium. Following this, incorporation will begin. An SG event near non-Core SCP-8487 has yet to be observed.
 _
**In traditional SCRIPT:** In paper, tablet, or other non-software text SCP-8487 remains relatively simple. For example, when introduced as SCP-8487-Core to a poem scratched onto a wall, the anomaly would likely become a basic "organism" with conceptually complex words centralized as a nucleus. This textual nucleus may be surrounded by a low-priority shell, or outstretching tendrils. Without a physical network or connection, it could not relocate on or from this wall. Non-grapheme based information[[footnote]] E.g. paintings or other images [[/footnote]] appear not to be SCRIPT. The proximity required for incorporation has been observed to scale with the size of graphemes.
Records recovered from ancient Rome and Greece indicate that at least four major libraries were purged after an SCP-8487 infection. Manifestation before this time is entirely unevidenced. Multiple accounts among Elizabethan historians of a "demon" corrupting their collections have been (tentatively) proposed as more recent infections.
 _
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-features-source |hover-enlarge=--]
|enlarge-amount=5
|speed=1
|float=true
|align=right
|width=40%
|url=https://i.imgur.com/nOscLSO.png
|add-caption=true
|caption=Hover to enlarge: Test 8487-5/92 Images #3 and #4. Image #4 was taken shortly before the shown text-editor's code was incorporated, rendering it unusable.
]]
**In software/digital SCRIPT:** Current Foundation understanding can be outlined as: if information would be SCRIPT written down, it will also be SCRIPT when encoded into electronic signals. The only confirmed requirement to this is that electronic SCRIPT must be transmitted or stored on intentionally crafted physical technology, disqualifying wireless communication. The following attributes have been observed exclusively from electronic SCP-8487 manifestation:
* Susceptibility to "delete" functions while hardware remains intact
* Distinct yet connected "organs" within the textual body
* Usage of "organs" in a system to produce more SCRIPT
* Complex nuclear architecture described by researchers as "neural"
* Tactical dismantling of non-hardwired "delete" functions
* Tactical dismantling of hostile AI agents
 _
Additionally, SCP-8487 appears able to sustain an electric charge for incorporated SCRIPT should its hardware lose power. The source of this energy is unknown. The charge is especially persistent for SCP-8487-Core, leading to the final character being impervious to deletion less than the destruction of its hardware.
 _
>  
